        <abstract> 
<p>The second volume of Lyell’s [<hi rend="italic">Principles</hi>, 10th ed.] gives a "fair history of the progress of opinion on Species".</p> 
            <p>Pleased by allusion to Pangenesis: "an untried hypothesis is always dangerous ground".</p>
            <p>Looks forward to chapter on domestication and on man.</p>
        </abstract>
